<HEADLINE>
FT  21 MAY 93 / Malaysian plan to set up new airline
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By KIERAN COOKE
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   KUALA LUMPUR
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
MALAYSIA says it intends to create an airline to operate on domestic and
international routes, writes Kieran Cooke in Kuala Lumpur.
Dr Mahathir Mohamad, prime minister, said the new airline was necessary
because Malaysia Airlines (MAS), the country's national carrier, was
expanding so fast that it had become 'overstretched'. He said the new
airline could be based on Pelangi Air, a small carrier which already
operates on some domestic and regional routes.
The prime minister said the government would not take up a stake in the
proposed new airline. 'We want the private sector to do business. We
regulate the business', said Dr Mahathir.
</TEXT>
