<TEXT>
ARGENTINA'S trade union congress has attacked the free market policies of
President Carlos Menem and raised the prospect of a general strike, 'when
and where it hurts the government the most,' Reuter reports from Buenos
Aires.
An assembly of 187 union delegates voted late on Wednesday to authorise Mr
