<HEADLINE>
FT  20 MAY 93 / International Company News in Brief: General Motors
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By PATRICK HARVERSON
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
General Motors said yesterday it had reached agreements with more than 100
banks on about Dollars 21bn of syndicated credit lines that together make up
about half of the group's total worldwide bank credit facilities, writes
Patrick Harverson. GM added that it was renegotiating about Dollars 4bn of
additional credit lines with banks in Europe, Canada and Australia.
The newly-negotiated syndications, which replace various individual bank
facilities extended to GM and GMAC, the group's financial services
subsidiary, represented a 'significant increase in the amount of committed,
long-term credit available to the corporation,' said GM.
